--- fastapi by default returns json as a response. If we want to change that we need to import and add HTMLResponse in decorator as follows
import fastapi.responses import HTMLResponse
@app.get('/',response_class=HTMLResponse)
in function we'll return f"<h1>{posts[0]['title']}</h1>"
--If we want same functionality after clicking /posts then we add another decorator below app.get. It will look like as:
@app.get('/',response_class=HTMLResponse)
@app.get('/posts',response_class=HTMLResponse)
